Description The DataPage class allows you to create a data transfer object that can be used to pass the results of a paginated query. This object contains items of the retrieved page.
Important points
 Most often, this object type is used to send responses to paginated queries. Pagination parameters are defined by a PagingParams object. The skip parameter in the PagingParams indicates how many items to skip. The takes parameter sets the number of items to return in the page. An optional total paramter allows you to specify the total number of items returned from a request. However, not all implementations support the total parameter because its generation may lead to severe performance implications.  Constructors Creates a new instance of data page and assigns its values.
