Description The ElasticSearchLogger class allows you to create loggers that dump execution logs to an ElasticSearch service.
Important points
 Elasticsearch is a popular search index. It is often used to store and index execution logs by itself or as a part of ELK (ElasticSearch - Logstash - Kibana) stack. Authentication is not supported in this version.  Configuration parameters  level: maximum log level to capture source: source (context) name  connection(s):
