Description The ErrorCategory defines the 12 standard error categories supported by the PipServices toolkit.
Constants Unknown Unknown or unexpected errors.
 Unknown: string = &ldquo;Unknown&rdquo;
 Internal Internal errors caused by programming mistakes.
 Internal: string = &ldquo;Internal&rdquo;
 Misconfiguration Errors related to mistakes in user-defined configurations.
 Misconfiguration: string = &ldquo;Misconfiguration&rdquo;
 InvalidState Errors caused by an incorrect object state.. For example: business calls when the component is not ready.
 InvalidState: string = &ldquo;InvalidState&rdquo;
 NoResponse Errors caused by remote calls timed out and not returning results. It allows to clearly separate communication related problems from other application errors.
 NoResponse: string = &ldquo;NoResponse&rdquo;
 FailedInvocation Errors caused by remote calls failed due to unidenfied reasons.
 FailedInvocation: string = &ldquo;FailedInvocation&rdquo;
 FileError Errors in read/write local disk operations.
 FileError: string = &ldquo;FileError&rdquo;
 BadRequest Errors due to incorrectly specified invocation parameters. For example: missing or incorrect parameters.
 BadRequest: string = &ldquo;BadRequest&rdquo;
 Unauthorized Access errors caused by missing user identity (authentication error) or incorrect security permissions (authorization error).
 Unauthorized: string = &ldquo;Unauthorized&rdquo;
 NotFound Errors caused by attempts to access missing objects.
 NotFound: string = &ldquo;NotFound&rdquo;
 Conflict Errors raised by conflicts between object versions that were posted by the user and those that are stored on the server.
 Conflict: string = &ldquo;Conflict&rdquo;
 Unsupported Errors caused by calls to unsupported or not yet implemented functionality.
 Unsupported: string = &ldquo;Unsupported&rdquo;

